# data-flow

## Player State Updates
- Progressive level-based timing system pushes updated cast/wait times to client
- Experience gain events trigger level progression checks
- Equipment purchases modify player inventory and balance
- Achievement progress updates broadcast to affected players

## Tournament Data Flow
- Registration data collected during initialization phase
- Real-time catch data updates tournament leaderboards
- Score multipliers (up to 3x) applied to qualifying catches
- Results and prizes distributed through broadcast system

## Seasonal/Progress Tracking
- Player statistics tracked across multiple categories:
  - Location access status
  - Equipment unlocks
  - Catch history by season
  - Tournament participation records
- Top 10 biggest catches maintained per player
- Session tracking data updated on connect/disconnect

## Broadcast Rules
- Special catches trigger global announcements
- Tournament catches silently update scoring
- Regular catches suppressed from broadcast
- Room-specific announcements limited to 8 players

## Bot Integration
- AI competitor data injected into player rooms
- Competitive catch rates synchronized with player progression
- Cat-themed personality data mapped to bot behaviors

