# data-flow

## Core State Management
- Fish state flows from `fishTypes.js` through catch detection to player collection
- Player progression updates trigger cascading achievement calculations
- Tournament state updates broadcast to participant leaderboards
- Water body parameters affect fish behavior and catch probability

## Achievement Flow
Achievement states flow through multiple systems:
1. Catch events -> Achievement processor
2. Achievement unlocks -> Player stats
3. Collection milestones -> Reward distribution
4. Tournament performance -> Seasonal tracking

## Tournament Data Pipeline
1. Entry registration -> Active participant pool
2. Catch validation -> Leaderboard updates 
3. Time-based rankings -> Prize distribution
4. Historical records -> Season aggregation

## Player State Updates
- Experience gains propagate through level calculation
- Stat modifications affect catch probabilities
- Collection updates trigger achievement checks
- Location unlocks enable new fish populations
- Equipment changes modify catch parameters

## Seasonal Tracking
- Tournament results aggregate into seasonal standings
- Catch records contribute to seasonal collections
- Achievement progress persists across seasons
- Location availability rotates seasonally

